“This green, which tempers the black, gives the shadows. The flesh thus apparent is made to live : he passes a rose colour over the cheeks, the lips, the eyelids, to lighten them and show the cir- culation of the blood there. Then the eyebrows appear under a deep brown, also the hair and beard, and then the outline of the face is determined.
